header.gameNote: TOP OF THE WORLD CLASSIC AT FAIRBANKS AK

article.headline: Rhode Island 92, Centenary 82
article.story: FAIRBANKS, Alaska (AP) -- Jimmy Baron scored 25 points and Rhode Island defeated Centenary 92-82 Sunday for fourth place in the BP Top of the World Classic. The Rams (3-2) bolted to a 13-point first-half lead, 18-5, with 15:37 remaining in the first half. Centenary (2-3) replied with a 14-3 scoring run, capped by Bryan Baumann's 3-pointer, and took its first lead 30-28 with 2:57 remaining. The Gents led 37-36 at halftime. Will Daniels' layup and free throw with 15:47 remaining in the second half gave Rhode Island the lead for good 47-46. Kahiem Seawright pulled down 13 rebounds and the Rams dominated the boards 41-29. They also shot 37-for-44 from the free throw line, including eight straight from Baron. Centenary hit 15-for-21 free throws. Iman Shokouhizadeh scored 19 points for Centenary. Lance Hill pulled down 6 rebounds. Joe Mbang added 21 points for Rhode Island.
